cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.CL 

The paper is focused on comparing four tree-based boosting algorithms for multi-class classification, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since these fields heavily rely on classification algorithms. Additionally, the paper uses publicly available datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories.
